      documentation: 'Alias of `foreach`. Self-repeating loop directive \u2014 the element with `each` IS the template that gets cloned for each item. Uses `"item in list"` syntax. The element is removed from the DOM and replaced by comment markers; clones are inserted between them as siblings.\n\n**Example:**\n```html\n<ul>\n  <li each="user in users" bind="user.name"></li>\n</ul>\n```\n\n**With filter/sort:**\n```html\n<li each="item in products" filter="item.price > 10" sort="name" limit="5" bind="item.name"></li>\n```\n\n**Empty list fallback (else="templateId"):**\n```html\n<li each="item in items" else="noItemsTpl" bind="item.name"></li>\n<template id="noItemsTpl"><li>No items found</li></template>\n```\nThe `else` template (bare id or `#id`) renders when the list is empty (`[]`) or null/undefined/not an array.\n\n**Loop context variables:** `$index`, `$count`, `$first`, `$last`, `$even`, `$odd`\n\n**Companions:** `index`, `filter`, `sort`, `limit`, `offset`, `template`, `else`, `key`, `animate-enter`, `animate-leave`, `animate-stagger`, `animate-duration`',
